{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863849885,"sessionID":"ses_28644a1e1ffeXevK8ggqv8mK5C","part":{"id":"prt_d79bbd0bf001gZemo5aaUnd5Qq","messageID":"msg_d79bbb190001fK0sfVNs8dUYgo","sessionID":"ses_28644a1e1ffeXevK8ggqv8mK5C","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011: Router JWT 认证与签发 - Task Checklist\n2: \n3: > **AR ID:** AR-011  \n4: > **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n5: > **Language:** Go  \n6: > **Size:** M  \n7: > **Stage:** ST-3 completed  \n8: > **Depends on:** AR-009 (Router HTTP Core), AR-010 (Session Management)\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## Task 1: Create JWT Types and Constants\n13: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt_types.go` with core type definitions\n14: \n15: - [ ] Create `jwt_types.go` file\n16: - [ ] Define `TokenClaims` struct with fields:\n17:   - `SessionID string` - Session identifier\n18:   - `UserID string` - User identifier (optional)\n19:   - `SandboxID string` - Associated sandbox ID\n20:   - `Namespace string` - Kubernetes namespace\n21:   - `RuntimeKind string` - Runtime type (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter)\n22: - [ ] Define `TokenPair` struct with `AccessToken` and `RefreshToken` fields\n23: - [ ] Define `TokenMetadata` struct with `IssuedAt`, `ExpiresAt`, `RefreshExpiresAt` fields\n24: - [ ] Define JWT constants:\n25:   - `TokenIssuer = \"agentcube-router\"`\n26:   - `AccessTokenExpiry = 5 * time.Minute`\n27:   - `RefreshTokenExpiry = 24 * time.Hour`\n28:   - `SecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n29: - [ ] Add JSON tags and documentation comments for all types\n30: - [ ] Write unit tests verifying type definitions and constants\n31: \n32: **Verification Command:**\n33: ```bash\n34: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTTypes\" && \\\n35: grep -E \"TokenClaims|TokenPair|TokenMetadata\" pkg/router/jwt_types.go\n36: ```\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## Task 2: Create JWT Error Types\n41: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt_errors.go` with error definitions\n42: \n43: - [ ] Create `jwt_errors.go` file (if not exists)\n44: - [ ] Define `JWTError` struct with Code, Message, Cause fields\n45: - [ ] Implement `Error() string` method\n46: - [ ] Implement `Unwrap() error` method\n47: - [ ] Define sentinel errors:\n48:   - `ErrTokenExpired` (code: TOKEN_EXPIRED)\n49:   - `ErrTokenInvalid` (code: TOKEN_INVALID)\n50:   - `ErrTokenSignatureInvalid` (code: TOKEN_SIGNATURE_INVALID)\n51:   - `ErrTokenMalformed` (code: TOKEN_MALFORMED)\n52:   - `ErrKeyNotFound` (code: KEY_NOT_FOUND)\n53:   - `ErrKeyGenerationFailed` (code: KEY_GENERATION_FAILED)\n54:   - `ErrSecretAccessFailed` (code: SECRET_ACCESS_FAILED)\n55: - [ ] Write unit tests verifying error creation and unwrapping\n56: \n57: **Verification Command:**\n58: ```bash\n59: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTError\" && \\\n60: grep \"ErrTokenExpired\\|ErrTokenInvalid\" pkg/router/jwt_errors.go\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## Task 3: Extend JWT Manager with Validation\n66: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt.go` with token validation methods\n67: \n68: - [ ] Implement `ValidateToken(tokenString string) (*TokenClaims, error)`:\n69:   - Parse JWT with RS256 signing method\n70:   - Verify signature using public key\n71:   - Extract and validate standard claims (exp, iat, iss)\n72:   - Extract custom claims (session_id, sandbox_id, etc.)\n73:   - Return `*TokenClaims` on success\n74:   - Return appropriate errors on failure\n75: - [ ] Implement `parseTokenClaims(claims jwt.MapClaims) (*TokenClaims, error)`:\n76:   - Extract session_id claim\n77:   - Extract sandbox_id claim\n78:   - Extract namespace claim\n79:   - Extract runtime_kind claim\n80:   - Validate required fields\n81: - [ ] Add context-aware validation method `ValidateTokenWithContext(ctx, token)`\n82: - [ ] Write unit tests:\n83:   - Valid token validation succeeds\n84:   - Expired token returns ErrTokenExpired\n85:   - Invalid signature returns ErrTokenSignatureInvalid\n86:   - Malformed token returns ErrTokenMalformed\n87:   - Missing claims returns appropriate error\n88: \n89: **Verification Command:**\n90: ```bash\n91: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTManager_Validate\"\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## Task 4: Implement Token Refresh Mechanism\n97: **Verifiable Output:** Token refresh functionality in JWTManager\n98: \n99: - [ ] Implement `GenerateTokenPair(claims map[string]interface{}) (*TokenPair, *TokenMetadata, error)`:\n100:   - Generate access token with 5-minute expiry\n101:   - Generate refresh token with 24-hour expiry\n102:   - Include jti (JWT ID) claim for refresh token tracking\n103:   - Return both tokens with metadata\n104: - [ ] Implement `RefreshToken(refreshToken string) (*TokenPair, *TokenMetadata, error)`:\n105:   - Validate refresh token signature and expiry\n106:   - Extract original claims\n107:   - Generate new token pair\n108:   - Return new access and refresh tokens\n109: - [ ] Implement refresh token rotation (optional security enhancement)\n110: - [ ] Write unit tests:\n111:   - Token pair generation succeeds\n112:   - Refresh token generates new valid pair\n113:   - Expired refresh token returns error\n114:   - Invalid refresh token returns error\n115: \n116: **Verification Command:**\n117: ```bash\n118: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTManager_Refresh\"\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ---\n122: \n123: ## Task 5: Create JWT Configuration Types\n124: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt_config.go` with configuration types\n125: \n126: - [ ] Create `jwt_config.go` file\n127: - [ ] Define `JWTConfig` struct with fields:\n128:   - `AccessTokenExpiry time.Duration`\n129:   - `RefreshTokenExpiry time.Duration`\n130:   - `RSAKeySize int` (default: 2048)\n131:   - `Issuer string`\n132:   - `SecretName string`\n133:   - `SecretNamespace string`\n134: - [ ] Implement `DefaultJWTConfig()` returning default configuration\n135: - [ ] Implement `JWTConfig.Validate()` method:\n136:   - Validate AccessTokenExpiry > 0\n137:   - Validate RefreshTokenExpiry > AccessTokenExpiry\n138:   - Validate RSAKeySize >= 2048\n139:   - Validate Issuer is not empty\n140: - [ ] Add environment variable support:\n141:   - `AGENTCUBE_JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRY`\n142:   - `AGENTCUBE_JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRY`\n143:   - `AGENTCUBE_JWT_SECRET_NAME`\n144: - [ ] Write unit tests for configuration validation\n145: \n146: **Verification Command:**\n147: ```bash\n148: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTConfig\"\n149: ```\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## Task 6: Implement JWT Middleware\n154: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt_middleware.go` with HTTP middleware\n155: \n156: - [ ] Create `jwt_middleware.go` file\n157: - [ ] Define `JWTMiddleware` struct with JWTManager field\n158: - [ ] Implement `NewJWTMiddleware(jwtManager *JWTManager) *JWTMiddleware`\n159: - [ ] Implement `Authenticate(next http.Handler) http.Handler`:\n160:   - Extract Authorization header (Bearer token)\n161:   - Validate token using JWTManager\n162:   - Store TokenClaims in request context\n163:   - Call next handler on success\n164:   - Return 401 on authentication failure\n165: - [ ] Implement `OptionalAuthenticate(next http.Handler) http.Handler`:\n166:   - Authenticate if token present\n167:   - Allow request through if no token\n168: - [ ] Implement `RequireSession(next http.Handler) http.Handler`:\n169:   - Verify session_id claim exists\n170:   - Verify session is valid (call session manager)\n171:   - Return 401 if session invalid\n172: - [ ] Write unit tests:\n173:   - Valid token passes authentication\n174:   - Missing token returns 401\n175:   - Invalid token returns 401\n176:   - Expired token returns 401\n177: \n178: **Verification Command:**\n179