Setup\n\n- [ ] _TBD: Task 1_\n- [ ] _TBD: Task 2_\n\n### Phase 2: Implementation\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/plan.md","time":{"start":1775863879216,"end":1775863879234}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863879238,"sessionID":"ses_28644a1e1ffeXevK8ggqv8mK5C","part":{"id":"prt_d79bc4d1e001Pbw7LsWiEWrTO3","messageID":"msg_d79bbe3e1001w34nLmg2PBQrSS","sessionID":"ses_28644a1e1ffeXevK8ggqv8mK5C","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 Design: Router JWT 认证与签发\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-011  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** Medium\n9: \n10: The JWT Manager provides secure, stateless authentication between the Router and sandbox pods using RSA-signed JWT tokens. It handles RSA key pair generation (2048-bit), RS256 token signing with configurable claims, and key persistence in Kubernetes Secrets for cluster-wide accessibility and pod restart resilience.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ### High-Level Design\n17: \n18: ```\n19: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n20: │                           JWT Manager Component                              │\n21: │                                                                              │\n22: │  ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────┐  │\n23: │  │  Key Generation │───▶│  Token Signing  │───▶│  Kubernetes Persistence │  │\n24: │  │  (RSA 2048)     │    │  (RS256)        │    │  (Secret Storage)       │  │\n25: │  └─────────────────┘    └─────────────────┘    └─────────────────────────┘  │\n26: │           │                      │                       │                   │\n27: │           ▼                      ▼                       ▼                   │\n28: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n29: │  │                       Router Server                                  │    │\n30: │  │  - Calls GenerateToken() for each proxied request                   │    │\n31: │  │  - Embeds session_id in JWT claims                                  │    │\n32: │  │  - Attaches Authorization: Bearer <token> header                    │    │\n33: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n34: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n35:                                     │\n36:                                     ▼\n37: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n38: │                           Sandbox Pod                                        │\n39: │  - Validates JWT signature using public key                                  │\n40: │  - Extracts session_id from claims                                           │\n41: │  - Processes authenticated request                                           │\n42: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n43: ```\n44: \n45: ### Component Interactions\n46: \n47: | Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n48: |-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n49: | **JWTManager** | Manages RSA keys and JWT signing | Claims map (`session_id`, etc.) | Signed JWT string |\n50: | **RSA Key Generator** | Creates cryptographically secure key pairs | rand.Reader, 2048 bits | Private/Public key pair |\n51: | **Token Generator** | Builds and signs JWT claims | Base claims + custom claims | RS256-signed token |\n52: | **Secret Manager** | Persists keys in Kubernetes | PEM-encoded keys | K8s Secret CRUD |\n53: | **Router Server** | Uses JWT for request authentication | Session info | Proxied request with JWT |\n54: \n55: ### Key Persistence Flow\n56: \n57: ```\n58: Server Startup\n59:      │\n60:      ▼\n61: NewJWTManager()\n62: (generate RSA key pair)\n63:      │\n64:      ▼\n65: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()\n66:      │\n67: ┌────┴─────────────────┐\n68: │                      │\n69: In-cluster?         Not in-cluster\n70: │                      │\n71: ▼                      ▼\n72: Create/Load Secret   Log warning\n73:      │               Use ephemeral keys\n74:      ▼\n75: Secret 'picod-router-identity'\n76: ├── private.pem (RSA PRIVATE KEY)\n77: └── public.pem  (PUBLIC KEY)\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### Token Generation Flow\n81: \n82: ```\n83: HTTP Request Received\n84:          │\n85:          ▼\n86: Session Resolved (via SessionManager)\n87:          │\n88:          ▼\n89: JWTManager.GenerateToken(claims)\n90:          │\n91:     ┌────┴────┐\n92:     ▼         ▼\n93: Base Claims   Custom Claims\n94: - exp         - session_id\n95: - iat         (from SessionInfo)\n96: - iss\n97:     │         │\n98:     └────┬────┘\n99:          ▼\n100: Sign with RS256\n101: (private key)\n102:          │\n103:          ▼\n104: Authorization: Bearer <token>\n105: (set on proxied request)\n106: ```\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ## Directory Structure\n111: \n112: ```\n113: pkg/router/\n114: ├── jwt.go              # JWTManager implementation - RSA key gen, token signing, secret storage\n115: ├── errors.go           # Error types including JWTSigningError\n116: ├── config.go           # Configuration including IdentityNamespace\n117: └── ...\n118: ```\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## Data Structures\n123: \n124: ### Core Types\n125: \n126: #### JWTManager\n127: \n128: ```go\n129: // JWTManager handles JWT key generation and token signing.\n130: type JWTManager struct {\n131:     privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n132:     publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n133:     clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n134: }\n135: ```\n136: \n137: | Field | Type | Description |\n138: |-------|------|-------------|\n139: | `privateKey` | `*rsa.PrivateKey` | RSA private key for RS256 signing |\n140: | `publicKey` | `*rsa.PublicKey` | RSA public key for signature verification |\n141: | `clientset` | `kubernetes.Interface` | Kubernetes client for Secret operations |\n142: \n143: ### Constants\n144: \n145: | Constant | Value | Description |\n146: |----------|-------|-------------|\n147: | `rsaKeySize` | `2048` | RSA key bit length |\n148: | `jwtExpiration` | `5 * time.Minute` | Default token validity duration |\n149: | `identitySecretName` | `\"picod-router-identity\"` | Kubernetes Secret name for key storage |\n150: | `privateKeyDataKey` | `\"private.pem\"` | Secret data key for private key |\n151: | `publicKeyDataKey` | `\"public.pem\"` | Secret data key for public key |\n152: \n153: ### Package Variables\n154: \n155: | Variable | Type | Default | Description |\n156: |----------|------|---------|-------------|\n157: | `IdentityNamespace` | `string` | `\"default\"` | Namespace for JWT secret storage, set from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var |\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## API Contracts\n162: \n163: ### Constructor\n164: \n165: ```go\n166: // NewJWTManager creates a new JWTManager with a generated RSA key pair.\n167: func NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error)\n168: ```\n169: \n170: **Behavior:**\n171: - Generates a new 2048-bit RSA key pair using cryptographically secure random source (`crypto/rand`)\n172: - Returns error with message \"failed to generate RSA key\" on failure\n173: - The `clientset` field is initially nil and set later by `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()`\n174: \n175: ### Token Operations\n176: \n177: ```go\n178: // GenerateToken creates a JWT with the given claims.\n179: func (m *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n180: ```\n181: \n182: **Behavior:**\n183: - Creates base claims: `exp` (now + 5 minutes), `iat` (now), `iss` (\"agentcube-router\")\n184: - Merges custom claims (e.g., `session_id` from SessionInfo)\n185: - Custom `exp` in claims overrides default expiration\n186: - Signs with RS256 using the private key\n187: - Returns error with message \"failed to sign token\" on signing failure\n188: \n189: ```go\n190: // GetPublicKeyPEM returns the public key in PKIX PEM format.\n191: func (m *JWTManager) GetPublicKeyPEM() ([]byte, error)\n192: ```\n193: \n194: **Behavior:**\n195: - Encodes public key using `x509.MarshalPKIXPublicKey`\n196: - Returns PEM block with type \"PUBLIC KEY\"\n197: - Returns error if marshaling fails\n198: \n199: ```go\n200: // GetPrivateKeyPEM returns the private key in PKCS#1 PEM format.\n201: func (m *JWTManager) GetPrivateKeyPEM() ([]byte, error)\n202: ```\n203: \n204: **Behavior:**\n205: - Encodes private key using `x509.MarshalPKCS1PrivateKey`\n206: - Returns PEM block with type \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\"\n207: \n208: ### Key Persistence Operations\n209: \n210: ```go\n211: // TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret attempts to store keys in K8s secret or load existing.\n212: func (m *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret() error\n213: ```\n214: \n215: **Behavior:**\n216: - Attempts to get in-cluster Kubernetes config via `rest.InClusterConfig()`\n217: - If not in-cluster: logs warning and returns nil (uses ephemeral keys)\n218: - Creates clientset and attempts to create Secret\n219: - If Secret already exists: loads existing keys and replaces ephemeral keys\n220: - Returns descriptive errors for client creation or secret operation failures\n221: \n222: **Secret Specification:**\n223: - Name: `picod-router-identity`\n224: - Namespace: `IdentityNamespace` (from env var or \"default\")\n225: - Type: `Opaque`\n226: - Labels: `app=agentcube`, `component=router`\n227: - Data keys: `private.pem`, `public.pem`\n228: \n229: ---\n230: \n231: ## Error Handling\n232: \n233: ### Error Types\n234: \n235: #### JWTSigningError\n236: \n237: ```go\n238: // JWTSigningError represents an error when JWT signing fails.\n239: type JWTSigningError struct {\n240:     Cause error\n241: }\n242: \n243: func (e *JWTSigningError) Error() string\n244: func NewJWTSigningError(cause error) *JWTSigningError\n245: ```\n246: \n247: Used in router handlers when token generation fails.\n248: \n249: ### Error Scenarios\n250: \n251: | Scenario | Error Message | Returned By |\n252: |----------|---------------|-------------|\n253: | RSA key generation failure | `failed to generate RSA key: %w` | `NewJWTManager()` |\n254: | Token signing failure | `failed to sign token: %w` | `GenerateToken()` |\n255: | Public key marshal failure | `failed to marshal public key: %w` | `GetPublicKeyPEM()` |\n256: | K8s client creation failure | `failed to create Kubernetes client: %w` | `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` |\n257: | Secret creation failure | `failed to create JWT secret: %w` | `createOrLoadSecret()` |\n258: | Existing secret retrieval failure | `failed to get existing JWT secret: %w` | `loadExistingSecret()` |\n259: | Missing private key in secret | `existing JWT secret missing private key data` | `loadExistingSecret()` |\n260: | PEM decode failure | `failed to decode PEM block` | `loadPrivateKeyPEM()` |\n261: | PKCS#1 parse failure | `failed to parse private key: %w` | `loadPrivateKeyPEM()` |\n262: \n263: ### Error Handling Strategy\n264: \n265: 1. **Key Generation Errors**: Fatal on startup - returns error to caller\n266: 2. **Token Signing Errors**: Returns wrapped error for handler to respond with 500\n267: 3. **K8s Client Errors**: Returns error for in-cluster failures; logs warning for non-cluster\n268: 4. **Secret Creation Errors**: Returns error except for `AlreadyExists` (triggers load)\n269: 5. **Key Loading Errors**: Returns error for malformed secret data\n270: \n271: ---\n272: \n273: ## Testing Strategy\n274: \n275: ### Unit Tests\n276: \n277: | Component | Test Cases | Expected Behavior |\n278: |-----------|------------|-------------------|\n279: | `NewJWTManager` | RSA key generation | Returns valid JWTManager with 2048-bit keys |\n280: | `NewJWTManager` | Random source | Uses `crypto/rand` for secure generation |\n281: | `GenerateToken` | Valid claims | Returns valid RS256-signed JWT string |\n282: | `GenerateToken` | Standard claims | Includes exp, iat, iss automatically |\n283: | `GenerateToken` | Custom claims | Merges session_id and other custom claims |\n284: | `GenerateToken` | Custom expiration | Custom exp overrides default 5 minutes |\n285: | `GenerateToken` | Signing error | Returns error with \"failed to sign token\" |\n286: | `GetPublicKeyPEM` | Valid encoding | Returns PKIX PEM with \"PUBLIC KEY\" header |\n287: | `GetPrivateKeyPEM` | Valid encoding | Returns PKCS#1 PEM with \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\" header |\n288: | `GetPublicKeyPEM`/`GetPrivateKeyPEM` | PEM format | Returns valid UTF-8, parseable by PEM decoders |\n289: \n290: ### Integration Tests\n291: \n292: | Scenario | Description |\n293: |----------|-------------|\n294: | Secret creation | Creates new Secret with correct labels and data |\n295: | Secret loading | Loads existing keys when Secret already exists |\n296: | Non-cluster mode | Returns nil error, logs warning for non-K8s environments |\n297: | Key persistence | Keys stored in Secret match generated keys |\n298: | Key retrieval | Loaded keys match previously stored keys |\n299: | Token validation | Generated tokens can be validated with stored public key |\n300: | Expired token | Tokens past exp claim fail validation |\n301: | Invalid signature | Tokens signed with different key fail validation |\n302: \n303: ### Mock Dependencies\n304: \n305: - `kubernetes.Interface` for Secret operations\n306: - `crypto/rand.Reader` can use deterministic source for reproducible tests\n307: \n308: ### Coverage Targets\n309: \n310: - Minimum: 80%\n311: - Target: 90%\n312: \n313: ---\n314: \n315: ## Dependencies\n316: \n317: ### Direct Dependencies\n318: \n319: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n320: |------------|---------|---------|\n321: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2.1 | JWT token creation and RS256 signing |\n322: | `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes client for Secret operations |\n323: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | v0.32.0 | Secret type definitions |\n324: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | v0.32.0 | K8s API error handling (AlreadyExists) |\n325: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | v0.32.0 | ObjectMeta, CreateOptions, etc. |\n326: | `k8s.io/client-go/rest` | v0.32.0 | In-cluster config detection |\n327: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.130.1 | Structured logging |\n328: \n329: ### Standard Library\n330: \n331: | Package | Purpose |\n332: |---------|---------|\n333: | `crypto/rand` | Cryptographically secure random number generation |\n334: | `crypto/rsa` | RSA key generation and signing |\n335: | `crypto/x509` | Key encoding/decoding (PKIX, PKCS#1) |\n336: | `encoding/pem` | PEM format encoding/decoding |\n337: | `fmt` | Error formatting |\n338: | `os` | Environment variable reading |\n339: | `time` | Token expiration timestamps |\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ## Configuration\n344: \n345: ### Environment Variables\n346: \n347: | Variable | Default | Description |\n348: |----------|---------|-------------|\n349: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace for JWT identity Secret |\n350: \n351: ### Configuration Flow\n352: \n353: ```go\n354: var IdentityNamespace = \"default\"\n355: \n356: func init() {\n357:     if ns := os.Getenv(\"AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\"); ns != \"\" {\n358:         IdentityNamespace = ns\n359:     }\n360: }\n361: ```\n362: \n363: ---\n364: \n365: ## Implementation Details\n366: \n367: ### RSA Key Generation\n368: \n369: ```go\n370: privateKey, err := rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, rsaKeySize)\n371: ```\n372: \n373: - Uses `crypto/rand.Reader` for secure random generation\n374: - 2048-bit key size provides balance of security and performance\n375: - Private key contains embedded public key\n376: \n377: ### Token Claims Structure\n378: \n379: ```json\n380: {\n381:     \"exp\": 1710000000,           // Expiration: now + 5 minutes\n382:     \"iat\": 1709999700,           // Issued at: current timestamp\n383:     \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",   // Issuer identifier\n384:     \"session_id\": \"sess-abc-123\" // Custom claim from SessionInfo\n385: }\n386: ```\n387: \n388: ### PEM Encoding\n389: \n390: **Private Key (PKCS#1):**\n391: ```\n392: -----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n393: <base64-encoded PKCS#1 data>\n394: -----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n395: ```\n396: \n397: **Public Key (PKIX):**\n398: ```\n399: -----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n400: <base64-encoded PKIX data>\n401: -----END PUBLIC KEY-----\n402: ```\n403: \n404: ### Kubernetes Secret Structure\n405: \n406: ```yaml\n407: apiVersion: v1\n408: kind: Secret\n409: metadata:\n410:   name: picod-router-identity\n411:   namespace: <AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE>\n412:   labels:\n413:     app: agentcube\n414:     component: router\n415: type: Opaque\n416: data:\n417:   private.pem: <base64-encoded PKCS#1 PEM>\n418:   public.pem: <base64-encoded PKIX PEM>\n419: ```\n420: \n421: ### Algorithm: RS256\n422: \n423: - **Signing**: RSA private key + SHA-256 hash\n424: - **Verification**: RSA public key + SHA-256 hash\n425: - **Key format**: PKCS#1 for private, PKIX for public\n426: - **Token format**: JWS Compact Serialization (header.payload.signature)\n427: \n428: ---\n429: \n430: ## Security Considerations\n431: \n432: ### Key Management\n433: \n434: 1. **Private Key Protection**: Private key never leaves the Router pod or K8s Secret\n435: 2. **Public Key Distribution**: Public key can be safely distributed to sandbox pods\n436: 3. **Secret Access**: Requires RBAC permission to create/get Secrets in target namespace\n437: 4. **Ephemeral Fallback**: Non-cluster environments use ephemeral keys (logged warning)\n438: \n439: ### Token Security\n440: \n441: 1. **Short-lived tokens**: 5-minute expiration limits exposure window\n442: 2. **Unique signatures**: RS256 ensures tokens cannot be forged without private key\n443: 3. **Session binding**: session_id claim ties token to specific session\n444: 4. **No refresh tokens**: Short expiration, session-level lifecycle management\n445: \n446: ### RBAC Requirements\n447: \n448: ```yaml\n449: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n450: kind: Role\n451: metadata:\n452:   name: agentcube-router-jwt\n453: rules:\n454: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n455:   resources: [\"secrets\"]\n456:   verbs: [\"create\", \"get\"]\n457:   resourceNames: [\"picod-router-identity\"]\n458: ```\n459: \n460: ---\n461: \n462: ## Migration Notes\n463: \n464: ### Adding JWT Support\n465: \n466: 1. **New dependency**: Already included in go.mod (`github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`)\n467: 2. **RBAC setup**: Ensure Router has Secret create/get permissions\n468: 3. **Namespace configuration**: Set `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` for non-default namespace\n469: 4. **Key rotation**: Delete `picod-router-identity` Secret to trigger new key generation\n470: \n471: ### Downstream Changes\n472: \n473: - Sandbox pods must validate JWT using public key from Secret\n474: - Public key can be mounted as volume from Secret or fetched via K8s API\n475: \n476: ---\n477: \n478: ## File Index\n479: \n480: | Path | Purpose |\n481: |------|---------|\n482: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager implementation with key generation, token signing, and secret storage |\n483: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | JWTSigningError and other error types |\n484: | `pkg/router/config.go` | IdentityNamespace configuration |\n485: \n486: ---\n487: \n488: ## References\n489: \n490: - [AR-009](changes/AR-009/design.md) — Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n491: - [AR-010](changes/AR-010/design.md) — Router Session Management\n492: - [Session Routing Design](../../session-routing/design.md) — Router design overview\n493: - [Client-Go Library](../../deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client usage\n494: - [JWT Specification](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519) — RFC 7519\n495: - [JWS Specification](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7515) — RFC 7515 (RS256)\n496: - [Delta Specification](delta-spec.md) — Detailed requirements and scenarios\n497: \n498: ---\n499: \n500: *AR-011 — Module: pkg/router — Language: Go — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 500 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 Design: Router JWT 认证与签发\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-011  \n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Medium\n\nThe JWT Manager provides secure, stateless authentication between the Router and sandbox pods using RSA-signed JWT tokens. It handles RSA key pair generation (2048-bit), RS256 token signing with configurable claims, and key persistence in Kubernetes Secrets for cluster-wide accessibility and pod restart resilience.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           JWT Manager Component                              │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/design.md","time":{"start":1775863879221,"end":1775863879236}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863879241,"sessionID":"ses_28644a1e1ffeXevK8ggqv8mK5C","part":{"id":"prt_d79bc51a5001gFAbVSlKjIHVad","messageID":"msg_d79bbe3e1001w34nLmg2PBQrSS","sessionID":"ses_28644a1e1ffeXevK8ggqv8mK5C","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/tests.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/tests.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011: Router JWT 认证与签发 - Test Specification\n2: \n3: ## Unit Tests\n4: \n5: ### JWT Token Generation\n6: \n7: - [ ] _TBD: Test RSA key pair generation_\n8: - [ ] _TBD: Test token signing with RSA-256_\n9: - [ ] _TBD: Test claims inclusion (exp, iat, iss, session_id)_\n10: \n11: ### JWT Token Validation\n12: \n13: - [ ] _TBD: Test valid token verification_\n14: - [ ] _TBD: Test expired token rejection_\n15: - [ ] _TBD: Test invalid signature rejection_\n16: \n17: ### RSA Key Management\n18: \n19: - [ ] _TBD: Test key storage in Kubernetes Secrets_\n20: - [ ] _TBD: Test key retrieval from Secrets_\n21: - [ ] _TBD: Test key generation on first startup_\n22: \n23: ### Token Refresh\n24: \n25: - [ ] _TBD: Test token refresh flow_\n26: - [ ] _TBD: Test refresh token validation_\n27: \n28: ## Integration Tests\n29: \n30: - [ ] _TBD: End-to-end JWT flow_\n31: - [ ] _TBD: Kubernetes Secret integration_\n32: - [ ] _TBD: Token lifecycle (generate, validate, refresh)_\n33: \n34: ## Performance Tests\n35: \n36: - [ ] _TBD: Token generation throughput_\n37: - [ ] _TBD: Token validation latency_\n38: \n39: ## Coverage Targets\n40: \n41: - Minimum coverage: 80%\n42: - Target coverage: 90%\n\n(End of file - total 42 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011: Router JWT 认证与签发 - Test Specification\n\n## Unit Tests\n\n### JWT Token Generation\n\n- [ ] _TBD: Test RSA key pair generation_\n- [ ] _TBD: Test token signing with RSA-256_\n- [ ] _TBD: Test claims inclusion (exp, iat, iss, session_id)_\n\n### JWT Token Validation\n\n- [ ] _TBD: Test valid token verification_\n- [ ] _TBD: Test expired token rejection_\n- [ ] _TBD: Test invalid signature rejection_\n\n### RSA Key Management\n\n- [ ] _TBD: Test key storage in Kubernetes Secrets_\n- [ ] _TBD: Test key retrieval from Secrets_","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/tests.md","time":{"start":1775863879223,"end":1775863879238}}}}
